The paper deals with entity extraction, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB). The use of crowdsourcing and statistical tools to optimize the extraction process suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also deals with natural language processing (cs.CL) in the form of queries and text processing.
